Qiao Shi Visits Art Exhibition of Chinese Paintings
BEIJING , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- Qiao Shi , chairman of the National People 's Congress Standing Committee , visited a painting exhibition at the China Art Gallery here today .
During his visit , Qiao spoke highly of " Vagrants " , a painting with the theme of patriotism , by Chinese painter Jiang Zhaohe .
The exhibition features 140 Chinese paintings collected by the Palace Museum and the art gallery .
On display are not only paintings by world-renowned modern artists such as Xu Beihong and Huang Zhou , but also famous works of ancient painters in the Ming and Qing dynasties ( 1368 - 1911 ) .
The exhibition , from February 18 to 28 , is sponsored by the Ministry of Culture , as part of the ' 98 China Year of International Fine Arts .
